<author><name><![CDATA[Gaurav]]></name></author>
<updated>2015-04-12T03:31:25-07:00</updated>
<published>2015-04-12T03:31:25-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=3403&amp;p=18779#p18779</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=3403&amp;p=18779#p18779"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: How To: Add A Horizontal Separator To Start Menu]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=3403&amp;p=18779#p18779"><![CDATA[
The pinned shortcuts are stored at C:\Users\&lt;user name&gt;\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\Windows\Start Menu\ or at C:\Users\&lt;user name&gt;\AppData\Roaming\ClassicShell\Pinned\. So creating a shortcut named &quot; ―――――――――――――――&quot; in that folder with a blank icon <em>is</em> your separator/heading.<br /><br />That is a simple but effective idea. If you put text in-between you can also categorize into groups. Looks like the headings that jump lists have.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Sun Apr 12, 2015 3:31 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
